{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0679f7bf456990e17048cdca401cf03b","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Caveman mode. Got enough info. BirthChart.chart has `planeta.sol`, `planeta.lua` (PosicaoPlaneta) and ascendente is number (degrees).\n\nNow I have all I need to plan the new akasha-core.ts. Let me also peek at the getSignoFromLongitude to understand sign names — but it's a non-exported helper, and the engines return lowercase pt names like 'aries', 'touro', etc.\n\nLet me now write the integrated version. I'll:\n1. Replace stub functions with real engine calls\n2. Add a helper for date conversion YYYY-MM-DD → DD/MM/YYYY\n3. Use real engine for sol_signo, lua_signo, lua_fase\n4. For asc_signo: convert ascendant (number) to sign\n5. For lat/lon: not available in AkashaInput → pass 0,0 (Atlantic ocean)\n\nImplementation:\n\n```ts\nasync function realPilar1Cabala(input: AkashaInput): Promise<PilarCabala> {\n  const { calcularCaminhoVida, getCiclosTemporais, calcularAnoPessoal } = await import('@akasha/core-cabala');\n  const [y, m, d] = input.data_nascimento.split('-').map(Number);\n  const ddmmyyyy = `${String(d).padStart(2, '0')}/${String(m).padStart(2, '0')}/${y}`;\n  // life_path\n  const lifePath = calcularCaminhoVida(ddmmyyyy);\n  // ano_pessoal\n  const anoPessoal = calcularAnoPessoal(ddmmyyyy).numero;\n  // ciclos\n  const ciclos = getCiclosTemporais(ddmmyyyy);\n  // birthday from day reduced\n  const reduzir = (n: number) => { while (n > 9 && n !== 11 && n !== 22 && n !== 33) n = String(n).split('').reduce((a,c) => a + Number(c), 0); return n; };\n  // expression from name length (kept from stub - cabala doesn't have expression in engine we imported)\n  return {\n    life_path: lifePath,\n    birthday: reduzir(d),\n    expression: reduzir(input.nome.replace(/\\s/g, '').length),\n    ano_pessoal: anoPessoal,\n  };\n}\n```\n\nWait — `expression` from numerology in the cabala engine uses different method (let me check). Actually let me just check if there's an expression function.","signature":"3c8ac6eff5b19f9ca4bed1d7eacd51b2790b12a71ef9b3bd258761c357621bab"}],"model":"MiniMax-M3","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard"},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19791390-f202-43ee-8249-6a90c45720df","uuid":"82520fcd-c0a2-4a20-b148-d03f61faa77f"}
